The paper deals with the density of languages accepted by various machine models, which is a topic in formal language theory (cs.FL). The use of reversal-bounded worktapes suggests a connection to data structures (cs.DS). The decidability results involve complexity classes such as PSPACE and L, which are topics in computational complexity theory (cs.CC). The paper also involves some logical reasoning and proof techniques, which are topics in mathematical logic (cs.LO) and information theory (cs.IT).
